npc1: The portal ahead takes you to Stage 3 — the Cyber Network.
npc1: If Stage 2 is the visible internet, Stage 3 is what runs underneath it. The infrastructure.
npc1: Data highways. Server clusters. Firewall Sentinels built to protect things that should never be protected.
npc1: The signal gets stronger the deeper you go. You're on the right path.
npc1: The Necromancer is not just hiding in the network. In a way, he IS the network.
npc1: Every server running a predatory gambling app. Every data packet moving money out of someone's account at 3 AM.
npc1: He built that layer. Or he corrupted it into what it is now. The line between those two things stopped mattering a long time ago.
npc1: You'll meet Firewall Sentinels in Stage 3. They are the system's immune response — they do not care about right or wrong, only about protecting the structure.
npc1: But there is something else in that layer. Something more dangerous than a Sentinel.
npc1: The system calls her the Collector. We call her the Witch.
npc1: She was the debt enforcement arm — built to track down people who borrowed money to keep gambling and could not pay it back.
npc1: She does not chase data. She chases people. And she remembers every name the algorithm ever marked as a debtor.
npc1: If she finds you in there, she will not let go easily.
npc1: The physical world's rules do not apply down there.
npc1: But the rules of mathematics do. And mathematics can be understood, reverse-engineered, and broken.
npc1: Go. Don't stop now.
